description:
Tremor is a motor symptom commonly referred to in the general population, but mainly affects the elderly population, when it presents in a very severe way, causes an inability to perform activities of daily living. In some cases, there is indicative of functional surgical procedures. The aim of the project is to propose a quantitative method for pre, intra and postoperative evaluation of tremor in the performance of functional surgical procedures, with the expectation that this evaluation may assist the multi professional team.  

 &nbsp; 

